Function for calculating moving average.¶

In [12]:
def moving_avg(df, window):
    for col in df.columns:
        df[f"{col}__window__mean"] = df[col].rolling(window=window).mean()
    df = df.dropna().reset_index(drop=True)
    return df

Decision Tree Regressor is used for prediction.¶

In [25]:
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeRegressor
from sklearn import metrics

regr = DecisionTreeRegressor(random_state=42)
regr.fit(X, y)
y_pred_dt = regr.predict(X_test)
dt_scores_regr = metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred_dt)
print(f"mean squared error is {dt_scores_regr}")
print('R^2:', metrics.r2_score(y_test, y_pred_dt))
print('Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE):', metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred_dt, squared=False))
